Package com.fasterxml.util.membuf.impl

Package that contains implementations of the API classes.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayBytesSegment
    BytesSegment implementation that uses POJAs (Plain Old Java Array) for storing byte sequences.
    ArrayBytesSegment.Allocator
    SegmentAllocator implementation that allocates ArrayBytesSegments.
    ArrayLongsSegment
    LongsSegment implementation that uses POJAs (Plain Old Java Array) for storing long sequences.
    ArrayLongsSegment.Allocator
    SegmentAllocator implementation that allocates ArrayLongsSegments.
    ByteBufferBytesSegment
    Segment implementation that uses ByteBuffers for storing data.
    ByteBufferBytesSegment.Allocator
    SegmentAllocator implementation that allocates ByteBufferBytesSegments.
    ByteBufferLongsSegment
    Segment implementation that uses LongBuffers for storing data.
    ByteBufferLongsSegment.Allocator
    SegmentAllocator implementation that allocates ByteBufferLongsSegments.
    ChunkyBytesMemBufferImpl
    ChunkyBytesMemBuffer implementation used for storing entries that are sequences of byte values, and are stored as distinct entries with definite size (as per ChunkyMemBuffer).
    ChunkyLongsMemBufferImpl
    MemBuffer implementation used for storing entries that are sequences of long values.
    StreamyBytesMemBufferImpl
    StreamyBytesMemBuffer implementation used for storing a sequence of byte values in a single byte sequence which does not retain boundaries implied by appends (as per StreamyMemBuffer).
    StreamyLongsMemBufferImpl
    StreamyBytesMemBuffer implementation used for storing a sequence of long values in a single long sequence which does not retain boundaries implied by appends (as per StreamyMemBuffer).
